## Purpose of This Document

This document locks the Treatment architecture for the Keeper platform — what Treatment is, how it is structured as JSON, how it is rendered by React, and where the two layers meet. It also defines TreatmentSurface, the first dynamic React component that reads Treatment JSON at runtime and responds to it — the component that makes Rendr's output visible.

This document emerged from the Design Board migration. Design Board is Rendr's home. Rendr's output needs a surface to render into. That surface is TreatmentSurface. This document defines both.

*Read this document before any build work touching Treatment, Rendr, Chronicle, the Design Board, or the right panel of any Universal Board.*

---

## 1. The Two-Layer Architecture

*Treatment JSON tells the platform what to deliver. TreatmentSurface is the React component that delivers it.*

These are two distinct layers. They must never be collapsed into one.

| Layer | What It Is |
| --- | --- |
| Treatment JSON | Named configuration. Produced by Rendr. Approved by the domain owner. Stored in domain JSON. Defines spatial ratios, motion character, density, presence, what surfaces, what recedes. This is data. |
| TreatmentSurface | A React component. Built by Cursor. Reads Treatment JSON at runtime. Expresses the values visually and behaviorally. Engages the correct motion library based on motion tier. This is code. |

The boundary between these layers is where Rendr's capability ends and Cursor's begins.

| Who | Can Do |
| --- | --- |
| Rendr | Adjust values within an existing TreatmentSurface. Change density, motion character, spatial ratios, presence behavior. Output Treatment JSON that a built component can read. |
| Cursor | Build new TreatmentSurface components. Extend existing ones. Wire motion libraries. Implement new rendering behavior that Treatment JSON cannot express alone. |
| Cloud | Review and flag when a Treatment JSON value requires a React code change to implement. Mark for Cloud Review in the IDE Board. |

