## 2. The Treatment JSON Schema

This is the bounded output target — what Rendr writes to, what TreatmentSurface reads from. Every field is a deliberate design decision.

### 2.1 Top-Level Structure

```typescript
interface TreatmentJSON {
  name: TreatmentName
  motionTier: MotionTier
  spatial: SpatialConfig
  motion: MotionConfig
  density: DensityConfig
  presence: PresenceConfig
  rationale?: string  // Rendr's plain-language explanation
}
```

### 2.2 Named Treatments

| Name | Character | Primary Motion | Use Context |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Minimal | Quiet, recessive, content-forward. Motion does not draw attention. | Framer Motion only | Reading, archival, focused work |
| Standard | Familiar, functional, directed. Motion confirms action. | GSAP | General platform use, domain boards |
| Cinematic | Immersive, directed, audience-forward. Motion leads. | Theatre.js | Journey playback, presentations |
| Immersive | Spatial, world-like, environmental. Motion is the environment. | R3F | Character agent worlds, Frogmore |

### 2.3 Motion Tier

| Tier | Library | What It Governs | Status |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Ambient (all tiers) | Framer Motion | Panel entry/exit, card appearance, micro-interactions. Baseline for all surfaces. | In stack |
| Standard | GSAP | Scroll choreography, directed purposeful motion, brand animation. | Directional |
| Cinematic | Theatre.js | Choreographed sequences, timeline-driven experiences, directed playback. | Directional |
| Immersive | R3F | 3D scenes as React components. Spatial worlds. Full environmental presence. | Directional |

### 2.4 Spatial Config

```typescript
interface SpatialConfig {
  panelRatios: number[]        // e.g. [1, 2, 1.5] — left, center, right
  contentMaxWidth: 'full' | 'reading' | 'compact'
  verticalRhythm: number       // Spacing unit multiplier
  atmosphereVisibility: number // 0.0 to 1.0
}
```

### 2.5 Motion Config

```typescript
interface MotionConfig {
  entryDuration: number        // Milliseconds
  exitDuration: number         // Milliseconds
  entryEasing: string          // e.g. 'easeOut', 'spring'
  stagger: number              // Milliseconds between sequential entries
  scrollBehavior: 'none' | 'parallax' | 'directed'
  transitionStyle: 'fade' | 'slide' | 'dissolve'
}
```

### 2.6 Density Config

```typescript
interface DensityConfig {
  level: 'compact' | 'default' | 'comfortable'
  breathing: number            // Multiplier on base vertical spacing unit
  informationDensity: 'minimal' | 'standard' | 'rich'
}
```

### 2.7 Presence Config

```typescript
interface PresenceConfig {
  primaryFocus: 'content' | 'context' | 'conversation'
  recessBehavior: 'fade' | 'compress' | 'none'
  idleState: 'ambient' | 'feed' | 'empty-named'
  contextShiftStyle: 'replace' | 'push' | 'dissolve'
}
```

