## 3. TreatmentSurface — The Dynamic React Component

*TreatmentSurface is one component. It reads Treatment JSON. It engages the right motion library. It renders the right presence behavior. It does not have behavior baked in.*

TreatmentSurface is the architectural answer to the question: how does Rendr's output become visible without requiring a rebuild every time Treatment changes?

The answer is that TreatmentSurface is a runtime interpreter. It receives a TreatmentJSON object as a prop and makes all rendering decisions from it. A domain owner changes Treatment through Rendr. The component responds. No Cursor session required.

### 3.1 Component Signature

```typescript
interface TreatmentSurfaceProps {
  treatment: TreatmentJSON
  content: TreatmentContent
  context?: TreatmentContext
  onContextShift?: (entry: PanelHistoryEntry) => void
}
```

### 3.2 Motion Library Resolution

TreatmentSurface resolves the correct motion library at runtime from `treatment.motionTier`. Framer Motion is always present as the ambient layer. Higher tier libraries are loaded conditionally.

| motionTier value | What TreatmentSurface does |
| --- | --- |
| `'ambient'` | Framer Motion only. Standard entry/exit transitions. No additional library loaded. |
| `'standard'` | Framer Motion for ambient. GSAP engaged for scroll and directed motion sequences. |
| `'cinematic'` | Framer Motion for ambient. Theatre.js engaged for choreographed timeline sequences. |
| `'immersive'` | Framer Motion for ambient. R3F engaged for 3D scene rendering. |

### 3.3 Chronicle — The First TreatmentSurface Instance

Chronicle is the right panel surface for Universal Boards. It is the first concrete implementation of TreatmentSurface. Its Treatment character is: warm, unhurried, aware of session history.

Chronicle at its baseline (Minimal/Ambient tier) uses Framer Motion. Lateral slide transitions at 200ms. Fields editable by default. Never empty at idle.

| Chronicle Element | What It Is |
| --- | --- |
| Trail Bar | Permanent history stack. Maximum three items visible. `...` compresses older history and is tappable. Sits at the top of the panel. |
| Feed Indicator | Soft dot + count at the right of the Trail Bar. 60-second polling minimum. Tapping loads the feed in the panel body. Not a notification badge. |
| Panel Body | Mini-router. Renders `panelHistory[currentIndex]`. Not a conditional branch tree. |
| Idle State | Named — `UniversalViewPanelIdle`. Never anonymous. Never empty. Shows domain ambient awareness. |
| Edit Behavior | Fields editable by default. No view/edit toggle. Debounced autosave or save on blur. |

