## 5. The Cascade

Treatment is assigned at any level of the platform hierarchy. The innermost active assignment wins.

| Level | Role |
| --- | --- |
| Domain | Sets the default Treatment for all Boards and surfaces within the domain. |
| Board | May declare its own Treatment, overriding the Domain default for that Board. |
| Frame | May declare its own Treatment, overriding the Board default for that Frame. |
| Audience | A Treatment may be defined for the audience-facing experience separately from the builder experience. |

Motion behavior follows this cascade exactly. A domain assigned Standard Treatment uses GSAP for directed motion, Framer Motion for ambient. A Board within that domain assigned Minimal Treatment overrides to Framer Motion only for that Board's surfaces.

