## 6. Design Board — The First TreatmentSurface Deployment

Design Board is Rendr's home. It is the first board where TreatmentSurface is the right panel. The migration of Design Board to Universal Board is the first concrete deployment of this architecture.

| Panel | Agent / Component | What Happens There |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Left | UniversalSwitcherPanel | Frames and Board Definitions. Selecting a Frame or Board Def drives the center and right panels. |
| Center | Rendr (Dialog Frame) | Conversation with Rendr about Treatment. Not Kip. The banner reflects what is in design focus. Kip accessible via Service Bar. |
| Right | TreatmentSurface / Keeper Canvas | Live preview of the selected Frame or Board with active Treatment applied. Rendr's output renders here. Eventually: drag-and-drop props, direct visual editing, spatial hotspot mapping. |

The Keeper Canvas — the right panel of Design Board at full capability — is a future state. Chronicle is the first TreatmentSurface instance. Keeper Canvas is what Chronicle becomes when Cinematic and Immersive tiers are live and Rendr has full generative capability.

