## 7. Build Sequence

In order. Do not skip steps. Each step is a prerequisite for the next.

| Step | What |
| --- | --- |
| 1 — This document | Treatment JSON schema defined and locked. TreatmentSurface architecture specified. Chronicle character defined. Cloud Review pattern named. |
| 2 — Chronicle build | Cursor builds Chronicle as the first TreatmentSurface instance. Framer Motion tier. Trail Bar, Feed Indicator, Panel Body, Idle State, Edit Behavior. Right panel on all Universal Boards. |
| 3 — Chronicle confirmed | All four boards show Chronicle in the right panel. Moment display has hierarchy and presence. Trail Bar navigates. Feed indicator is ambient. |
| 4 — Design Board migration | Design Board migrates to Universal Board. Rendr as center agent. TreatmentSurface as right panel. Left panel as UniversalSwitcherPanel with Frames and Board Definitions. |
| 5 — Rendr schema | Rendr's system prompt and output schema defined against TreatmentJSON. Rendr can produce valid Treatment JSON that TreatmentSurface renders. |
| 6 — GSAP / Theatre.js | Standard and Cinematic tiers installed after SSR compatibility confirmed and performance targets named. TreatmentSurface extended to engage them from motionTier value. |

